## PURPOSE
Generate .mdx files under /content/ that render through /project/[slug]
using getMDXComponents. Rules derived from existing project files.

---

## FILE STRUCTURE

- One .mdx file per project at /content/{slug}.mdx
- Filename = route slug, lowercase kebab-case
- Every file begins with imports (if any), then a metadata export

---

## METADATA CONTRACT

export const metadata = {
  title: string,              // Project name, max 60 chars
  role: string,               // Your role ("UI/UX Designer", "Full-Stack Developer")
  type: string,               // Category: "Design" | "Engineering" | "Business"
  description: string,        // 1-2 sentence summary, renders at 2xl. Max 250 chars
  date: string,               // ISO format YYYY-MM-DD, year is extracted for display
  tags: string[],             // 2-6 tags from the TAGS constant or custom strings
  additionalLinks: [          // External links array, can be empty []
    { label: string, url: string }
  ],
  image: string,              // Hero media: /projects/{slug}/filename.{ext}
  previewImage: string,       // Card preview media (can match image)
  featured: boolean,          // Whether to feature on homepage
  priority: number            // Sort order for featured projects (1 = highest)
}

Rules:
- ALL fields are required, no optional omissions
- Media paths live under /projects/{slug}/ (not /images/)
- Supported media: .png, .jpg, .webp, .webm, .mp4
- If no external links exist, use an empty array: []
- Import shared constants when applicable (e.g., TAGS)

---

## AVAILABLE CUSTOM COMPONENTS

Only these components are available beyond standard markdown:

### <Image />
  Props: src (string), width (number), height (number), alt (string, required),
         className? (string), caption? (string)
  Notes:
  - alt text is mandatory and descriptive
  - caption prop renders styled caption text beneath the image
  - className supports Tailwind utilities including dark mode variants
  - For dark-mode-adaptive diagrams, use:
    className="invert hue-rotate-180 dark:invert-0 dark:hue-rotate-0"

### <Video />
  Props: src (string)
  Notes:
  - Use for .webm or .mp4 inline video

### <ImageMarquee />
  Props: folder (string), direction ("left" | "right")
  Notes:
  - Auto-reads all images from the specified public folder
  - Use in pairs with alternating directions for visual rhythm

---

## INLINE HTML USAGE

Raw HTML with Tailwind is permitted for layout when no component exists:

### Grid layouts for side-by-side images:
  <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2 md:gap-8 -mb-8">
    <Image ... />
    <Image ... />
    <Image ... />
  </div>

### Manual captions (when not using Image caption prop):
  <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2 mb-16">
    Caption text here
  </div>

### Vertical spacing:
  <div className="my-12" />

Rules:
- Only use raw HTML for layout grids, spacing, and caption overrides
- Always use Tailwind classes, never inline style attributes
- Prefer the Image caption prop over manual caption divs when possible

